FBIS4-61859 "drsov091_b_94016" FBIS-SOV-94-091 Daily Report 11 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Military Expenditure Increased in Draft 1994 Budget Military Expenditure Increased in Draft 1994 Budget LD1105075894 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 11 May 94 LD1105075894 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] The expenditure of the military-industrial complex in the draft federal 1994 budget has been increased from 37 trillion to 50 trillion rubles. The draft is scheduled to be considered today by the State Duma. Aleksandr Piskunov, deputy chairman of the Duma defense committee, said the amendment was introduced after a roundtable meeting of deputies and government members. The meeting was convened on 5 May after a personal request by Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin to President Boris Yeltsin.
